\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {7}{\ignorespaces Residual distributions (predicted \(-\) true, dex) per fold, with best-fit normal curves and their \((\mu , \sigma )\) annotated. Distribution widths decrease monotonically with \(G_0\); per-fold means lie between \(-0.16\) and \(+0.16\,\text  {dex}\) after mass calibration. The multi-modal structure at several folds means the Gaussian curves summarise location and scale only and should not be read as a claim of normality.}}{11}{figure.7}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:residuals}{{7}{11}{Residual distributions (predicted \(-\) true, dex) per fold, with best-fit normal curves and their \((\mu , \sigma )\) annotated. Distribution widths decrease monotonically with \(\Gzero \); per-fold means lie between \(-0.16\) and \(+0.16\dex \) after mass calibration. The multi-modal structure at several folds means the Gaussian curves summarise location and scale only and should not be read as a claim of normality}{figure.7}{}}
