\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {8}{\ignorespaces Density-stratified error analysis of the deployed pipeline. \emph  {(a)} \(R^2\) on the subset of cells above a minimum-density percentile: \(R^2\) \emph  {decreases} toward the dense tail because the within-subset target variance shrinks faster than the errors. \emph  {(b)} Fraction of cells with absolute residual below fixed thresholds versus \(G_0\); the dip at \(G_0= 0.8\) reflects that fold's residual \(+0.16\,\text  {dex}\) bias. \emph  {(c)} MAE per true-density decile: errors peak in the low-density deciles of the low-\(G_0\) folds, at the steep atomic-to-molecular transition; high-\(G_0\) folds are flat at \(\,\rlap  {\raise 0.5ex\hbox {$<$}}{\lower 1.0ex\hbox {$\sim $}}\,\)0.1\,\text  {dex}. \emph  {(d)} \(R^2\) within the top-\(N\) per cent densest cells.}}{12}{figure.8}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:stratified}{{8}{12}{Density-stratified error analysis of the deployed pipeline. \emph {(a)} \(\Rsq \) on the subset of cells above a minimum-density percentile: \(\Rsq \) \emph {decreases} toward the dense tail because the within-subset target variance shrinks faster than the errors. \emph {(b)} Fraction of cells with absolute residual below fixed thresholds versus \(\Gzero \); the dip at \(\Gzero = 0.8\) reflects that fold's residual \(+0.16\dex \) bias. \emph {(c)} MAE per true-density decile: errors peak in the low-density deciles of the low-\(\Gzero \) folds, at the steep atomic-to-molecular transition; high-\(\Gzero \) folds are flat at \(\la \)0.1\dex . \emph {(d)} \(\Rsq \) within the top-\(N\) per cent densest cells}{figure.8}{}}
